===Noun===
'''rite of passage'''
#a ceremony or series of ceremonies, often very ritualized, to celebrate a transition in a person's life.  Baptisms, weddings and funerals are among the best known examples.
#:'''Examples:''' After John offically attained his majority, Robert took him his first legal beer, this is a common American rite of passage.

